TITLE: New Infinite Scroll Implementation with disabled Property
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the updated approach for infinite scroll where the disabled property is set directly on the target element, replacing the enable() method.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ionic-team/ionic-framework/blob/main/BREAKING_ARCHIVE/v4.md#2025-04-16_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: html
CODE:
```
<ion-infinite-scroll (ionInfinite)="doInfinite($event)">
  <ion-infinite-scroll-content></ion-infinite-scroll-content>
</ion-infinite-scroll>
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
doInfinite(event) {
  console.log('Begin async operation');

  setTimeout(() => {
    console.log('Async operation has ended');
    event.target.complete();

    // To disable the infinite scroll
    event.target.disabled = true;
  }, 500);
}
```

